e: In light of Blearchie's lack of flames..here goes.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Wasn't that the goal of the START 1 and START 2 treaties? Or is this only different in calling for the disarming of ALL warheads?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Start I and II were a step in the right direction, but statistically, they havent solved much. We still have massive amounts of nuclear weapons sitting out there. And yes, the difference in my suggestion is an immediate removal of all nuclear weapons, because, Start III hasnt happened...and it'll take Start 50 before we're anywhere close to being entirely disarmed.<br><br>Start II Was introduced in 93...it took 8 years for Russia's Duma to even vote on the damned thing. How long until they get their shit together and vote on start III? Its too much bullshit, just disarm and get it over with. <p><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=62888" target = "_blank">Drakz Soulsnacks</a><br>BlackRage Gravelord</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umirajtheenchanter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miraj the Enchanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/9/02 7:46:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1656.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In light of Blearchie's lack of flames..here goes.</span><hr size=1> ok, better idea<br><br>how about you disarm deez nuts in your mouth. <p><img src=http://members.aol.com/mirajenchanter/smash.jpg><BR><BR>Board Ops<img src=http://www.members.aol.com/mirajenchanter/whack.gif>Your Sig</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/unydiaywalmoriel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nydia Ywalmoriel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/9/02 8:04:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1656.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In light of Blearchie's lack of flames..here goes.</span><hr size=1> Drakz:<br><br>I'm *really* tired at the moment (was about to head for bed, long day of travelling tomorrow), but it seems to me that there would be a great deal of resistance to disarming by either the US or Russia, despite the enormous amount of sense it would make, in the current climate.   With Pakistan, India, China, and possibly North Korea all in the nuclear club, not to mention the current level of terrorism hysteria and concern about 'rogue states', I expect that if any change is actually made in America's nuclear policy, it will be only at whom our thousands of nukes are pointed, rather than any significant change in their actual numbers.  While I agree with the famous statement 'One cannot simultaneously prevent and prepare for war', this is a case where 'leading by example', especially given the perceived risks involved, is going to be a very hard sell... <br><br>And while Russia's predicament is frightening, at least Putin has a pretty good idea, and some semblance of control, over what goes on in the military, having been a former KGB man (and a strong leader) himself.  What is far scarier is the situation in the former soviet republics in central Asia that formerly had huge nuclear stockpiles.  Who knows how many of these have already been sold, and to whom?<br><br>Regards,<br>Nydia Ywalmoriel<br>Autonomous Collective    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uselwensoulgazer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Selwen Soulgazer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ayonae Vice</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/9/02 9:35:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1656.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.colba.net/~xtlee/images/fistc03.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In light of Blearchie's lack of flames..here goes.</span><hr size=1> Umm its not the Russians im scared of ,its the middle eastern countries that are getting these nukes that Im afraid of.Those crazy bastards think that dying while killing innocent people is honorable and their duty to god.At least the russians dont want to die.<br> If there was a nuclear war wed all die anyway.Doesnt matter who started it or why.The people that survive the first strikes will get to enjoy a nuclear winter where they will either starve to death or die of radiation poisoning.<br> Thats fuckin pleasant aint it? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>   <font color= ffoooo>Selwen SoulGazer</font > <BR>High Priest <i>"Maturity is not learned through isolation,but in the mirror of relationship."</i><BR> <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=261328>Selwens Gear</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umalse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/9/02 10:39:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1656.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In light of Blearchie's lack of flames..here goes.</span><hr size=1> Nuclear weapons are never going to go away until we have mechanisms that make their deployment too expensive for the intended goal.<br><br>Not to sound like I'm advocating that Star Wars crap (which was little more than thinly disguised Federal subsidies), but this sort of sentiment has been expressed before, just as vociferously -- about automatic rifles and machine guns, between the American Civil War and the first World War. Unfortunately for the activists and those on the receiving end, rifles and man-portable machine guns are still the single most cost effective weapon available to anyone with a vested interest in applying lethal force. Unsurprisingly, every combat force in the world uses them. These weapons changed the cost of deploying previously effecient forces like cavalry such that they don't exist anymore. Eventually, the technology of blowing stuff up and killing people is going to change so that we have something that reduces the effectiveness of nuclear weapons to below the point that keeping an arsenal of them is worthwhile.<br><br>You can't unmake a thing, and no amount of policy bullshit is going to change the fundamental cost/benefit relationship it has.<br><br>On another note -- those nuclear arsenals are double-edged insurance that no foreign army will ever set foot on US (or Chinese, or certain parts of Russian) soil, so you're likely gauranteed to be spared the possibilty of ever having to live through an invasion, and I'll bet Poland or Britain would have taken on the sad mantle of MAD politics for that in 1939. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulummusl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LummusL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/9/02 12:10:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1656.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In light of Blearchie's lack of flames..here goes.</span><hr size=1>       Nukes are mainly just a deterant. Nobody wants to use them because they don't even make sense from a tactical stand point and only serve to induce terror. If you look back through history, most wars were fought in oder to gain control of land. Land is the single most precious commodity other than time, since there isn't exactly any more real estate being maunfactured. Land contains all the resources to support nations. Denotation of thermo nuclear fusion weapons over land renders the land uninhabital for decades as well as allowing radiation to get into the atmosphere and in return return into earth as radioactive rain and fallout that gets into the water table. Thus the land is no long habital nor aerable and the population that would have tended it either by farming, mining or residing upon it as a work force would have been either vaporized, rendered sickly and cancerous, or fled the attack.<br>      Thus after all your effort in building a vast arsonal of these weapons, if you ever actually dared to launch a couple, you have everything to lose and nothing to gain. You in turn destroy the land that you either wanted to defend or occupy and thats the whole concept behind MAD. We as Americans know it. The Chinese know it. The Russians know it. Those who may not know it are rogue states that believe that killing others while making a martar out of themselves is a free ride to the grace of Allah and perhaps India and Pakistan who spent billions on a nuclear program while their nation's people live in squaller. <p><img src=http://personal.atl.bellsouth.net/~bielawat/pictures/sigF.bmp usemap=#sig border=0><map name=sig><area shape=rect coords=0,0,185,150  alt="Summul's Stuff" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=165316><area shape=rect coords=265,0,450,150 alt="Lummus's Stuff"href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=165129><area shape=rect coords=185,0,265,150 alt="Final Destiny"href=http://www.final-